herencia roberto r  the wall street transcript roberto r herencia roberto r herencia is the president of banco popular north america the us banking subsidiary of popular inc with executive offices based out of rosemont illinois he is responsible for the daytoday operations of bpna’s branch network in six states and all of its lending and leasing activities mr herencia also supervises the operations of popular cash express a financial services superstore providing basic financial services to low and moderateincome consumers with more than  locations in six states from  through  mr herencia was the us senior credit officer and head of the us credit products division of banco popular de puerto rico mr herencia is an executive vice president of popular inc and its main subsidiary banco popular de puerto rico he is a member of the corporation’s senior management council responsible for the management of the corporation’s banking operations and merger and acquisition activity in the us mainland prior to joining banco popular in  mr herencia spent  years with the first national bank of chicago currently bank one he joined first chicago in  as part of its credit training program spending four years in mexico as a corporate banking associate and assistant manager from  to  he was an assistant vice president and deputy senior credit officer for latin america in  he became vice president and the team leader responsible for the restructure of problem assets in mexico brazil venezuela and the philippines in  as vice president and head of the emerging markets division he was in charge of first chicago’s operations in latin america mr herencia is a member of the board of directors of banco popular north america equity one popular cash express popular north america and banco popular national association he is a trustee of wttw inc the museum of science and industry and le moyne college he is a director of the junior achievement of chicago and a member of depaul university’s college of commerce advisory council in addition mr herencia was recently appointed director on the board of the servicemaster company in addition he is a recipient of the ellis island medal of freedom mr herencia graduated magna cum laude and received his bachelor’s degree in finance from georgetown university he received his mba from the kellogg school of management at northwestern university related interviewsroberto herencia  banco popular north america bpop bpopaugust   cartlatest newsjames abate of centre asset management sees consumer demand driving new stock highsmalcolm e polley of stewart capital and how to play the health care stockstimothy biltz ceo of lumos networks identifies the key component for future g networksthe wall street transcript is a completely unique resource for investors and business researchersover  ceo equity analyst and money manager interviewssubscribe nowsign up for newsletter weekly email with new indepth interviews email most popular interviewsdelivering longterm results with a riskmanaged growth fundjames a abate published july   in investing strategiescompanies covered amat jnj coh rl cog nvda adbe atvi klac amzn nflx goog fb glw mu   wfm jwn cmg gps eqt rice spls buy finding investments with favorable risk and reward opportunitieshenry beukema published july   in investing strategiescompanies covered orcl msft nsrgy amzn wfm lrlcy agn lnr buy better returns and lower risk in the midcap spacemalcolm e polley published july   in investing strategiescompanies covered praa hurn fii fl nke amzn wfm wba rad buy most popular reportswireless communications  telecom published july  buy investing strategies published july  buy investing strategies published june  buy  top company interviews register for a free account to gain greater access to the wall street transcript right now ceo interviewsinterview with the president and ceo lumos networks corp nasdaqlmosinterview with the corporate vp of business development strategy and investor relation