ed across six states  prior to joining popular mr herencia spent  years with the first national bank of chicago now jp morgan chase in a variety of roles including deputy senior credit officer and head of the emerging markets division mr herencia is a trustee of the museum of science and industry depaul university and northwestern memorial foundation in chicago  he serves on the board of directors of junior achievement of chicago the navy pier corporation in chicago operation hope in los angeles and new america alliance  mr herencia is a former member of the board of directors of the servicemaster company a registered public corporation nyse svm where he served as chairman of its audit and finance committee mr herencia has received numerous awards for his civic contributions including the distinguished corporate citizenship award from the jewish council on urban affairs the evy award from a silver lining foundation and the prestigious ellis island medal of honor a native of puerto rico mr herencia graduated magna cum laude and received his bsba in finance from georgetown university  he received his mba from the kellogg school of management at northwestern university overview opic history frequently asked questions board of directorsboard meetings board resolutions projects pending board approval executive staff our investment policies office of accountability transparency information quality guidelines careers roberto herencia metropolitan bank group profile  biography  bloomberg feedback roberto herencia chairman metropolitan bank group career history chairman metropolitan bank group present presidentceo bxm holdings inc present senior exec vpcoo banco popular sa  head household intl inc  presidentceo midwest banc holdings inc unknown presidentceo midwest bank  trust coelmwood park il unknown president banco popular north america unknown executive vice president popular inc unknown various positions first natl bank of chicago former chief executive officer banco po